#. <html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta author="Bhikkhu Brahmali"><meta content="Pali text from the Mahāsaṅgīti Tipiṭaka Buddhavasse 2500" name="description"><title></title></head><body><div id="text" lang="en"><section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: Saṃ­ghā­di­sesa­kaṇḍa → añña­bhāgi­ya­sikkhā­pada (kaṅkhāvitaraṇī)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Saṃ­ghā­di­sesa­kaṇḍa"
msgstr "Monks’ Suspension"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Dutiya­duṭṭha­dosa­sikkhā­pada"
msgstr "9. The second training rule on anger"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.167"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.288"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-ss.9.1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.9.1.1"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1626"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalanda­ka­nivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrel sanctuary."

#. See Suspension 8, <ref>MS.1.1565</ref>, for a comment on the present rendering of these names.
#. VAR: chagalakaṃ → chakalakaṃ (si, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena metti­ya­bhūma­jakā bhikkhū gijjhakūṭā pabbatā "
"orohantā addasaṃsu chagalakaṃ ajikāya vippa­ṭi­pajjan­taṃ."
msgstr ""
"On one occasion the monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka were descending from Mount "
"Vulture Peak, when they saw two goats copulating."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.3"
msgid "Disvāna evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "They said to each other,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.4"
msgid "“handa mayaṃ, āvuso, imaṃ chagalakaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ nāma karoma."
msgstr "“Let’s give the he-goat the name Dabba the Mallian"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.5"
msgid "Imaṃ ajikaṃ mettiyaṃ nāma bhikkhuniṃ karoma."
msgstr "and the she-goat the name Mettiya the nun."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.6"
msgid "Evaṃ mayaṃ voharissāma."
msgstr "We can then say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.7"
msgid "Pubbe mayaṃ, āvuso, dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ sutena avocumhā."
msgstr "‘Earlier we spoke because of what we had heard about Dabba,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.8"
msgid ""
"Idāni pana amhehi sāmaṃ diṭṭho mettiyāya bhikkhuniyā vippa­ṭi­pajjanto”ti."
msgstr "but now we’ve seen him ourselves copulating with the nun Mettiya.’”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.9"
msgid "Te taṃ chagalakaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ nāma akaṃsu."
msgstr "They gave them those names"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.10"
msgid "Taṃ ajikaṃ mettiyaṃ nāma bhikkhuniṃ akaṃsu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.11"
msgid "Te bhikkhūnaṃ ārocesuṃ—"
msgstr "and then told the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.12"
msgid "“pubbe mayaṃ, āvuso, dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ sutena avocumhā."
msgstr "“Earlier we spoke about what we had heard,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.13"
msgid ""
"Idāni pana amhehi sāmaṃ diṭṭho mettiyāya bhikkhuniyā vippa­ṭi­pajjanto”ti."
msgstr "but now we’ve seen Dabba copulating with the nun Mettiya.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.14"
msgid "Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "The monks replied,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.15"
msgid "“māvuso, evaṃ avacuttha."
msgstr "“Don’t say such a thing."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.16"
msgid "Nāyasmā dabbo mallaputto evaṃ karissatī”ti."
msgstr "Venerable Dabba wouldn’t do that.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1627"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.17"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "The monks told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.18"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṃghaṃ "
"sannipātāpetvā āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ paṭipucchi—"
msgstr "The Master had the Order of monks assembled and asked Dabba,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.19"
msgid "“sarasi tvaṃ, dabba, evarūpaṃ kattā yathayime bhikkhū āhaṃsū”ti?"
msgstr "“Dabba, do you remember doing as these monks say?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.20"
msgid "“Yathā maṃ, bhante, bhagavā jānātī”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable Sir, the Master knows about me.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.21"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "A second"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.22"
msgid "tatiyampi kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and a third time the Master asked"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.23"
msgid "“sarasi tvaṃ, dabba, evarūpaṃ kattā yathayime bhikkhū āhaṃsū”ti?"
msgstr "the same question"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.24"
msgid "“Yathā maṃ, bhante, bhagavā jānātī”ti."
msgstr "and got the same response."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.289"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.25"
msgid "“Na kho, dabba, dabbā evaṃ nibbeṭhenti."
msgstr "He then said, “Dabba, the Dabbas don’t give such evasive answers."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.26"
msgid "Sace tayā kataṃ katanti vadehi,"
msgstr "If it was done by you, say so;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.27"
msgid "sace tayā akataṃ akatanti vadehī”ti."
msgstr "if it wasn’t done by you, then say that.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.28"
msgid ""
"“Yato ahaṃ, bhante, jāto nābhijānāmi supinantenapi methunadhammaṃ "
"paṭisevitā, pageva jāgaro”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Venerable Sir, since I was born I don’t recall having sexual intercourse "
"even in a dream, much less when I was awake.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.29"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi—“tena hi, bhikkhave, ime bhikkhū "
"anuyuñjathā”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, monks, call those monks to account,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.1.30"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvā bhagavā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ pāvisi."
msgstr "and he rose from his seat and entered his dwelling."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.9.1.2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1628"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.2.1"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū metti­ya­bhūma­jake bhikkhū anuyuñjiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"The monks then questioned Mettiya and Bhūmajaka, who told them what had "
"happened."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.2.2"
msgid "Te bhikkhūhi anuyuñjīyamānā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ—"
msgstr "The monks said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.2.3"
msgid ""
"“kiṃ pana tumhe, āvuso, āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ aññabhāgiyassa "
"adhikaraṇassa kiñci desaṃ lesamattaṃ upādāya pārājikena dhammena "
"anuddhaṃsethā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Did you accuse Venerable Dabba of an offense entailing expulsion, using an "
"unrelated legal issue as a pretext?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.2.4"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti."
msgstr "“Yes.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.2.5"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.2.6"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.2.7"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma metti­ya­bhūma­jakā bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ "
"aññabhāgiyassa adhikaraṇassa kiñci desaṃ lesamattaṃ upādāya pārājikena "
"dhammena anuddhaṃ­ses­santī”ti."
msgstr "“How can Mettiya and Bhūmajaka accuse Venerable Dabba like this?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1629"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.2.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū metti­ya­bhūma­jake bhikkhū aneka­pariyā­yena "
"vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They rebuked those monks in many ways and then told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.2.9"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ aññabhāgiyassa "
"adhikaraṇassa kiñci desaṃ lesamattaṃ upādāya pārājikena dhammena "
"anuddhaṃsethā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"He said, “Is it true, monks, that you accused Dabba the Mallian of an "
"offense entailing expulsion, using an unrelated legal issue as a pretext?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.2.10"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.2.11"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.2.12"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ aññabhāgiyassa "
"adhikaraṇassa kiñci desaṃ lesamattaṃ upādāya pārājikena dhammena "
"anuddhaṃ­ses­sa­tha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you accuse Dabba like this?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.2.13"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.2.14"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.2.14a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.168"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1630"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.290"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.2.15"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ duṭṭho doso appatīto aññabhāgiyassa adhikaraṇassa "
"kiñci desaṃ lesamattaṃ upādāya pārājikena dhammena anuddhaṃseyya—"
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk who is angry and displeased, using an unrelated legal issue as a "
"pretext, accuses another monk of an offense entailing expulsion,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.2.16"
msgid "‘appeva nāma naṃ imamhā brahmacariyā cāveyyan’ti."
msgstr "aiming to make him leave the monastic life,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.2.17"
msgid ""
"Tato aparena samayena sama­nug­gāhīya­māno vā asama­nug­gāhīya­māno vā "
"añña­bhāgi­yañ­ceva taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ hoti koci deso lesamatto upādinno, "
"bhikkhu ca dosaṃ patiṭṭhāti, saṃghādiseso”ti."
msgstr ""
"and then after some time, whether he is questioned or not, it is clear that "
"the legal issue is unrelated and used as a pretext, and he admits to his ill-"
"will, he commits an offense entailing suspension.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs1.2.18"
msgid "(<em>9</em>:<strong>13</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-ss.9.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.9.2.1"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1631"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1632"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs2.1.6"
msgid "Bhikkhunti"
msgstr "Another monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs2.1.7"
msgid "aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ."
msgstr "a different monk."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1633"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs2.1.8"
msgid "Duṭṭho dosoti"
msgstr "Angry:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs2.1.9"
msgid "kupito anattamano anabhiraddho āhatacitto khilajāto."
msgstr "upset, dissatisfied, discontent, having hatred, hostile."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1634"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs2.1.10"
msgid "Appatītoti"
msgstr "Displeased:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs2.1.11"
msgid ""
"tena ca kopena, tena ca dosena, tāya ca anattamanatāya, tāya ca "
"anabhiraddhiyā appatīto hoti."
msgstr ""
"because of that upset, that ill-will, that dissatisfaction, and that "
"discontent, he is displeased."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.9.2.2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1635"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs2.2.1"
msgid "Aññabhāgiyassa adhikaraṇassāti"
msgstr "An unrelated legal issue:"

#. </span></p><div class="gloss"><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs2.2.2"
msgid "āpattañ­ña­bhāgi­yaṃ vā hoti adhika­ra­ṇañ­ña­bhāgi­yaṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"It is either unrelated in regard to offenses or unrelated in regard to legal "
"issues."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs2.2.3"
msgid "Kathaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ adhikaraṇassa aññabhāgiyaṃ?"
msgstr "How is a legal issue unrelated to a legal issue?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs2.2.4"
msgid ""
"Vivā­dādhika­ra­ṇaṃ anuvā­dādhika­ra­ṇassa āpat­tādhika­ra­ṇassa "
"kic­cādhika­ra­ṇassa aññabhāgiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"A legal issue arising from a dispute is unrelated to a legal issue arising "
"from an accusation, a legal issue arising from an offense, and a legal issue "
"arising from a proceeding."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs2.2.5"
msgid ""
"Anuvā­dādhika­ra­ṇaṃ āpat­tādhika­ra­ṇassa kic­cādhika­ra­ṇassa "
"vivā­dādhika­ra­ṇassa aññabhāgiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"A legal issue arising from an accusation is unrelated to a legal issue "
"arising from an offense, a legal issue arising from a proceeding, and a "
"legal issue arising from a dispute."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs2.2.6"
msgid ""
"Āpat­tādhika­ra­ṇaṃ kic­cādhika­ra­ṇassa vivā­dādhika­ra­ṇassa "
"anuvā­dādhika­ra­ṇassa aññabhāgiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"A legal issue arising from an offense is unrelated to a legal issue arising "
"from a proceeding, a legal issue arising from a dispute, and a legal issue "
"arising from an accusation."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs2.2.7"
msgid ""
"Kic­cādhika­ra­ṇaṃ vivā­dādhika­ra­ṇassa anuvā­dādhika­ra­ṇassa "
"āpat­tādhika­ra­ṇassa aññabhāgiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"A legal issue arising from a proceeding is unrelated to a legal issue "
"arising from a dispute, a legal issue arising from an accusation, and a "
"legal issue arising from an offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs2.2.8"
msgid "Evaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ adhikaraṇassa aññabhāgiyaṃ."
msgstr "It is in this way that a legal issue is unrelated to a legal issue."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1636"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs2.2.9"
msgid "Kathaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ adhikaraṇassa tabbhāgiyaṃ?"
msgstr "How is a legal issue related to a legal issue?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs2.2.10"
msgid "Vivā­dādhika­ra­ṇaṃ vivā­dādhika­ra­ṇassa tabbhāgiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"A legal issue arising from a dispute is related to a legal issue arising "
"from a dispute."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs2.2.11"
msgid "Anuvā­dādhika­ra­ṇaṃ anuvā­dādhika­ra­ṇassa tabbhāgiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"A legal issue arising from an accusation is related to a legal issue arising "
"from an accusation."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs2.2.12"
msgid ""
"Āpat­tādhika­ra­ṇaṃ āpat­tādhika­ra­ṇassa siyā tabbhāgiyaṃ siyā aññabhāgiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"A legal issue arising from an offense may be either related or unrelated to "
"a legal issue arising from an offense."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1637"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss9:pts-cs2.2.13"
msgid "Kathaṃ āpat­tādhika­ra­ṇaṃ āpat­tādhika­ra­ṇassa aññabhāgiyaṃ?"
msgstr ""
"How is a legal issue arising from an offense unrelated to a legal issue "
"arising from an offense?"

